@startuml
title System Use Case Diagram - Auth and Workspace Access (Masar)

left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam actorStyle awesome
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #F8FAFC
  BorderColor #2D3748
}
skinparam usecase {
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  BorderColor #2D3748
  ArrowColor #2D3748
}

actor "Visitor /\nUnauthenticated User" as Visitor
actor "Invited User" as InvitedUser
actor "Workspace Member" as Member
actor "Workspace Manager\n(Owner/Admin)" as WorkspaceManager <<abstract>>
actor "Workspace Owner" as Owner
actor "Workspace Admin" as Admin
actor "Email Provider\n(Hostinger SMTP)" as EmailProvider

Owner --|> WorkspaceManager
Admin --|> WorkspaceManager
WorkspaceManager --|> Member
InvitedUser --|> Visitor

rectangle "Masar - CRM Support SaaS" as System {
  (Sign Up) as UCSignup
  (Send Email\nVerification OTP) as UCSendVerifyOtp
  (Resend OTP) as UCResendOtp
  (Verify Email) as UCVerifyEmail
  (Log In) as UCLogin
  (Refresh Access\nToken) as UCRefresh
  (View Current\nUser Context) as UCMe
  (Update Profile) as UCProfile
  (Change Password) as UCChangePassword
  (Request Password\nReset OTP) as UCForgotPassword
  (Reset Password) as UCResetPassword
  (Log Out Current\nSession) as UCLogout
  (Log Out All\nSessions) as UCLogoutAll
  (List My\nWorkspaces) as UCListMine
  (Switch Active\nWorkspace) as UCSwitch
  (Create Workspace\nInvite) as UCCreateInvite
  (List Workspace\nInvites) as UCListInvites
  (View Workspace\nInvite) as UCViewInvite
  (Resend Workspace\nInvite) as UCResendInvite
  (Revoke Workspace\nInvite) as UCRevokeInvite
  (Accept Workspace\nInvite) as UCAcceptInvite
}

Visitor -right-> UCSignup
Visitor -right-> UCResendOtp
Visitor -right-> UCVerifyEmail
Visitor -right-> UCLogin
Visitor -right-> UCForgotPassword
Visitor -right-> UCResetPassword

InvitedUser -right-> UCAcceptInvite
InvitedUser -right-> UCVerifyEmail

Member -right-> UCRefresh
Member -right-> UCMe
Member -right-> UCProfile
Member -right-> UCChangePassword
Member -right-> UCLogout
Member -right-> UCLogoutAll
Member -right-> UCListMine
Member -right-> UCSwitch

WorkspaceManager -left-> UCCreateInvite
WorkspaceManager -left-> UCListInvites
WorkspaceManager -left-> UCViewInvite
WorkspaceManager -left-> UCResendInvite
WorkspaceManager -left-> UCRevokeInvite

EmailProvider -left-> UCSendVerifyOtp
EmailProvider -left-> UCResendOtp
EmailProvider -left-> UCForgotPassword
EmailProvider -left-> UCCreateInvite
EmailProvider -left-> UCResendInvite
EmailProvider -left-> UCAcceptInvite

UCSignup .right.> UCSendVerifyOtp : <<include>>
UCResendOtp .up.> UCSendVerifyOtp : <<extend>>

note right of UCSwitch
Only this use case changes the
active workspace for a session
and returns a fresh access token.
end note

note bottom of UCAcceptInvite
Invite acceptance creates or activates
membership but does not auto-switch
an existing active workspace session.
end note

@enduml
